# Sidebar Collapsed View Shortcuts

Add circular shortcut buttons to the sidebar when it is in its collapsed state, allowing users to switch categories without expanding the sidebar.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The sidebar width in collapsed mode is 60px. The circular buttons will be centered in this space.

## Proposed Changes

### GeminiLauncher

#### [MODIFY] [ResourcesPage.xaml](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/ResourcesPage.xaml)
- Add a new `StackPanel` named `CollapsedSidebarContent` inside the Sidebar Border.
- Set its initial [Opacity](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/SettingsPage.xaml.cs#303-313) to 0 and [Visibility](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/SettingsPage.xaml.cs#324-332) to `Collapsed`.
- Create circular [RadioButton](file:///C:/Users/Linyizhi/.gemini/GeminiLauncher/Views/VersionSettingsDialog.xaml.cs#445-456) styles for the collapsed state.
- Update the `SidebarToggle` triggers to cross-fade between `SidebarContent` and `CollapsedSidebarContent`.
- Implement circular buttons for:
  - Mod (🧩)
  - Modpack (📦)
  - Resourcepack (🖼️)
  - Shader (☀️)
  - Datapack (🏷️)
  - View More (➕/Icon)

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Expand and collapse the sidebar using the toggle button.
- Verify that the full text fades out and the circular icons fade in smoothly.
- Test clicking each circular icon to ensure it switches the category correctly.
- Verify the "View More" functionality from the collapsed state.
- Check aesthetic consistency with the iOS style.
